race.comment: Hard to fault the recent form of BUFFET BUSTER (5) with a string of top three finishes, including a win two back. Rider has a great record while aboard and placed only try course and distance. Expected to run well. KING'S HALO (1) was going well, including a near miss here two back then was safely held here in open class latest. Course and distance winner back in grade and worth another try. NIPPA'S NIGHTCAP (3) is another in great form. Just missed two back then scored last time. Tricky gate but expected to give a sight. PRINCE AKEEM (8) is overdue for a win and rarely misses the frame here with a win and five minors from nine tries. Back in grade and among the main chances. TRAPEZE PLEASURE (7) motored home strongly and wasn't far away last time. Looks hard to hold out late.
